docs.abstract: The social media company, facing criticism from governments around the world, also offered evidence that its automated systems are improving.
docs.snippet: The social media company, facing criticism from governments around the world, also offered evidence that its automated systems are improving.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Facebook, facing withering criticism from governments around the world, said Thursday that it had been more aggressive in recent months about scrubbing its platform of hate speech.

headline.main: Facebook Says It Is More Aggressively Enforcing Content Rules
headline.print_headline: Hate Content Is Targeted For Removal By Facebook

docs.abstract: The Trump administration announced an aid package for farmers on Thursday to mollify an important political constituency hurt by a trade clash with China.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration announced an aid package for farmers on Thursday to mollify an important political constituency hurt by a trade clash with China.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Thursday unveiled a $16 billion bailout for farmers hurt by his trade war with Beijing, signaling a protracted fight ahead that is already prompting some American companies to shift business away from China.

headline.main: Trump Gives Farmers $16 Billion in Aid Amid Prolonged China Trade War
headline.print_headline: Farmers Stung By Trade Strife Get $16 Billion

docs.abstract: The Halcyons from Janus Motorcycles, assembled in an old dry cleaner’s shop in Goshen, Ind., look like machines built back in the town’s heyday.
docs.snippet: The Halcyons from Janus Motorcycles, assembled in an old dry cleaner’s shop in Goshen, Ind., look like machines built back in the town’s heyday.
docs.lead_paragraph: GOSHEN, Ind. — Downtown Goshen looks much the same as it did when American-built motorcycles from the likes of Merkel, Thor and Henderson first startled horse traffic.

headline.main: Motorcycles With One Foot in the Future and One in the Past

byline.original: By Mark Gardiner and David Kasnic

docs.abstract: At its annual shareholders meeting, the bank’s chairman faced pressure to resign amid a money-laundering scandal and meager profits.
docs.snippet: At its annual shareholders meeting, the bank’s chairman faced pressure to resign amid a money-laundering scandal and meager profits.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — Deutsche Bank shareholders had plenty of reasons to be unhappy as they converged in a Frankfurt concert hall Thursday for the troubled lender’s annual meeting.

headline.main: Deutsche Bank Leaders, Facing Angry Investors, Survive Vote
headline.print_headline: Deutsche Bank Leaders, Facing Angry Shareholders, Survive Vote

docs.abstract: The Fed is continuing its “patient” stance as it considers its next move, but weak inflation could force it to walk a policy tightrope.
docs.snippet: The Fed is continuing its “patient” stance as it considers its next move, but weak inflation could force it to walk a policy tightrope.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Reserve left interest rates unchanged on Wednesday, and its chairman, Jerome H. Powell, stressed that it would remain patient, even as investors looked for a rate cut and President Trump urged one.

headline.main: Fed Leaves Interest Rates Unchanged as Low Inflation Persists
headline.print_headline: Fed Leaves Interest Rates Unchanged Amid Low Inflation

docs.abstract: Indigo is expanding to the United States with its new model for how a big bookstore chain can thrive in the era of online retail.
docs.snippet: Indigo is expanding to the United States with its new model for how a big bookstore chain can thrive in the era of online retail.
docs.lead_paragraph: About a decade ago, Heather Reisman, the chief executive of Canada’s largest bookstore chain, was having tea with the novelist Margaret Atwood when Ms. Atwood inadvertently gave her an idea for a new product.

headline.main: How a Canadian Chain Is Reinventing Book Selling

docs.abstract: For people without a college degree, finding work that offers decent pay can be a challenge. The solution may require a change in scenery.
docs.snippet: For people without a college degree, finding work that offers decent pay can be a challenge. The solution may require a change in scenery.
docs.lead_paragraph: You dropped out of college, or decided straight out of high school that college was not your thing. Here’s some advice if you are looking for a job: Stay out of Washington. Don’t go to New York. Forget about San Francisco. If you want to make anything near a decent wage, head for Toledo, Des Moines or Birmingham.

docs.abstract: The California utility disclosed in a filing that securities regulators are looking into how it disclosed and accounted for losses from fires in recent years.
docs.snippet: The California utility disclosed in a filing that securities regulators are looking into how it disclosed and accounted for losses from fires in recent years.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The Securities and Exchange Commission has opened an investigation into Pacific Gas and Electric’s accounting for its losses related to three years of wildfires in Northern California, the utility reported to shareholders Thursday.

headline.main: PG&E Says S.E.C. Is Investigating Its Wildfire Disclosures

docs.abstract: Occidental’s proposal remained at $76 a share. But that announcement and an earlier one that it would sell off some Anadarko investments were meant to counter Chevron’s bid.
docs.snippet: Occidental’s proposal remained at $76 a share. But that announcement and an earlier one that it would sell off some Anadarko investments were meant to counter Chevron’s bid.
docs.lead_paragraph: HOUSTON — Occidental Petroleum fortified its bid for Anadarko Petroleum on Sunday night with more cash in its latest effort to outbid Chevron and win the support of Anadarko’s shareholders who may well make the final decision on a merger.

headline.main: Occidental Ups Its Cash Offer for Anadarko
headline.print_headline: Occidental Ups Cash Bid To Acquire Anadarko
